chunks.html_content:
You can no longer register free NHS polymerase chain reaction (PCR) tests online.

If you have an old NHS PCR test and the instructions tell you to register it, do not use it. You will not be able to register it or get the result if you send it off. Get a new test instead.

You can buy COVID-19 tests from shops and pharmacies, including online.

You may be able to get free rapid lateral flow tests from your local pharmacy if you’re eligible for COVID-19 treatments.
